{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/support-for-adult-carers/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"f9f3c9c8-020e-5782-9821-b44616e11be0","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 5a0863e7-1a26-4540-8f54-ac4000b1e436 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 5a0863e7-1a26-4540-8f54-ac4000b1e436 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 4165c76b-49f4-430a-921f-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field c9d7dce7-d8ba-4fc5-82c8-ac4000b1e436 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field c9d7dce7-d8ba-4fc5-82c8-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field 63eab6ed-e4f4-46b9-afd2-ac4000b1e436 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 63eab6ed-e4f4-46b9-afd2-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field 87fab605-6477-475b-9c1c-ac4000b1e436 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 87fab605-6477-475b-9c1c-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field ed0bed41-39fb-496a-9da6-ac4000b1e436 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field ed0bed41-39fb-496a-9da6-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field a3436061-1a51-4946-8f97-ac4000b1e436 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field a3436061-1a51-4946-8f97-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- begin field 28b51169-0ab5-460b-9604-ac4000b1e436 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 28b51169-0ab5-460b-9604-ac4000b1e436 --><!-- end item 4165c76b-49f4-430a-921f-ac4000b1e436 -->","topic":{"id":"8a0dcd0d-457e-51f3-bb8d-cb9abed98985","topicId":"535a2cb2-ac55-4c42-ba32-ac4000b1d290","topicName":"Support for adult carers","slug":"support-for-adult-carers","lastRevised":"November 2020","chapters":[{"id":"c8031010-eeca-5ec2-8a2b-5fb3ca2eb166","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"69ec7c8f-cf0d-5dbd-b893-89c2650a72ca","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"49a3aecb-d0b2-58e2-8ec3-fe94f2a9132b","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"936b3c23-1c2f-5003-9f5d-05e063485d44","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"77adc050-2665-545f-89b0-60ee6b0c8116","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"6a2556ad-0860-52f0-a8a0-c57cd81f9263","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"edeeef30-2db3-5c88-8e49-e79f62b6fd87","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"b9e9f803-c81a-59fb-81b0-3e9fcbd97741","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"118bcee7-0fd7-5dad-954c-1746972d2785","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemNa